{"questionId":"9073864","questionHtml":"<p>Explain the condition for <em>w</em> that eliminates reflection for a particular light wavelength in&nbsp;air <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>air</mtext></msub></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«to eliminate reflection» destructive interference is required <strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p>phase change is the same at both boundaries / no relative phase change due to reflections <strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p>therefore&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>w</mi><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>coating</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>air</mtext></msub></math></p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>coating</mtext></msub><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>air</mtext></msub><mrow><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>coating</mtext></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;✓<br></em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073864","referenceCode":"21M.2.HL.TZ1.b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Explain the condition for w that eliminates reflection for a particular light wavelength in air λair.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.3 – Interference","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}